descript.abstract: King County School Sites and School Related Facilities
descript.purpose: Parcel-based centroid for school facility. No footprint or infrastructure extent provided. Attributes assign parcel and street identifiers for location information.

dataqual.logic: Generally one point for each named school
dataqual.complete: Contains schools for all public school districts within King County, as well as private schools and colleges. Point features also represent closed schools or school owned properties - this data is less complete than the existing schools.

horizpa.horizpar: Points aligned to school buildings using digital air photography (where possible).

procstep.procdesc: Corrections made for: Creekside – Exists in SCHSITE at stated address. Corrected missing ESITE. Location Good Panther Lake School – Kent – Exists in SCHSITE but incorrect address. Address, XY and ESITE corrected Skyline HS – Exists in SCHSITE at stated address. Corrected missing ESITE. Location Good Cedar River School – Exists in SCHSITE at stated address. Elementary corrected to Junior High/Middle. Location Good
Updated name and location for Pacific Cascade Freshman Campus (now Pacific Cascade Middle School). Updated location for Louisa May Alcott School.
Updated with latest information as of December 2005, reflecting new schools, school closures and school changes (for public elementary and secondary schools only).
Points aligned to correct parcel and / or correct location using air photography
Original data geocoded using school addresses against street network
Rename current MAINT.GISC.PointsInterest.SCHSITE_POINT feature class to MAINT.GISC.PointsInterest.SCHSITE_MAST.

Create new lookup table from SCHSITEPAT_LXT called SCHSITE_TYPE. Contains only items SCH_CLASS (small integer 5) and CLASS_DESC (text 50). Values from old items CLASS and DESC calculated to new items, respectively. Items OLDTYPE, SYMBOL and DUP are not carried forward from old lookup table to new table. Finally in new table, remove all records other than where CLASS (now SCH_CLASS) is 1:9.
Updated addresses for Maplewood Heights Elementary and Sierra Heights Elementary due to Renton August 2010 annexation. New addresses match Renton addressing scheme.
Changed schema (item names) as follows: 1. CLASS to SCH_CLASS, 2. PREFIX to DIR_PREFIX, 3. STREET to ST_NAME, 4. SUFFIX to DIR_SUFFIX, 5. SOURCE to DAT_SOURCE
Updated with corrections for Lake Washington School District. Corrections to address, ADDRESS_POINT.esite id assignments. Added new school: Rachel Carson

Updated with corrections for Issaquah and Snoqualmie Valley SD. Corrections to address, ADDRESS_POINT.esite id assignments. Added new schools: Creekside Elementary, Grand Ridge Elementary, Cascade View Elementary, and Twin Falls Middle School

Create python routine \\gisimages\image\pythonscripts\KCGISCenter\schsite.py that creates a join between feature class SCHSITE_MAST and table SCHSITE_TYPE. Join is performed on SCHSITE_MAST.CLASS to SCHSITE_TYPE.CLASS. CLASS_DESC item from SCHSITE_TYPE table is added to SCHSITE_MAST. SCHSITE_MAST is renamed to SCHSITE_POINT and posted from feature dataset MAINT.GISC.PointsInterestProcess. Any future updates to SCHSITE_MAST should be made against the version in MAINT.GISC.PointsInterest feature data set. After updates are completed, python script should be run to complete table managment. Reimport metadata from master and repost data to SDW.
Derived from COMMON_INTEREST master table based on CODE = 660,661,662,663,664 or 665. Business table attributes are then attached.

Complete data review performed in 2010. Edits compiled in database on Process Date. New domain added to current set of 660-665. Value 666 added to uniquely classify K-12 grade schools. Previously this had been inferred through SCH_CLASS item. SCH_CLASS item repurposed to solely designated whether site is Public, Private or Vacated. This item had previously stored mixed information regarding public or private status and class of school. Class of school is now managed via CODE. CLASS_DESC is dropped. This had been the literal for SCH_CLASS. When SCH_CLASS was repurposed, this item no longer was necessary. DISTNUM is dropped. This had been the numeric equivalent of what is stored in DISTRICT. COMMENTS is dropped. LONG_CEN and LAT_CEN, geographic coordinates for Longitude and Latitude of the feature centroid are added to allow geocoding through County Data Portal site.
